The DOM and Events 

DOM = Document Object Model 
      : an interface for interacting with HTML documents
      : basic javascript commands to create, modify, style, and delete elements in the DOM

//Adding functionality to website using Javascript 
//Event Handlers Overview 
//Registerimg an onclick event to button 
//DOM methods to modify attributes and styles of HTML elements, and define a callback function

Topics : 
a. DOM
b. Selectors
c. Manipulating the DOM 
d. Event Listeners 


\\Nodes
-each entry is called a node in the tree
-root node : top node in the tree
-parent node : node which has another node inside it
-child node : node directly inside another node 

\\DOM Manipulation 
 - javascript allows us to add interactivity to our websites
 -allows our websited to respond to user input 
 -allows to update HTML tags 
 -allows to change aspects of CSS of page
 -allows to collect information the user has added to the page 
 -allows to make the webpage interactive
 
